HEADWORD: Canard
<hw>Ca*nard"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., properly, a
duck.]</ety> <def>An extravagant or absurd report or story; a fabricated
sensational report or statement; esp. one set afloat in the newspapers
to hoax the public.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Canarese</ent>⟦br⟧
